The paper discusses polynomial representations of Boolean functions, which is a topic closely related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of Ramsey Theory suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), while the study of symmetric functions and the lower bound for non-degenerated functions may involve topics in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
